records.addlTxt:
Terry Miller Jr appears by video. Attorney Megan Kaldunski appears by video. Attorney Careen Gordon appears in person for the State of Wisconsin.
Bench warrant issued 10/26/2022 is cancelled. Court orders case adjourned for a preliminary hearing.

Defendant Terry Miller Jr not in court.  Attorney Sarah Zwach appeared by video for Terry Miller Jr.  Attorney Thomas L. Potter appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for preliminary hearing. State's witness is present. Defense counsel has no explanation for defendant's non-appearance. State requests bench warrant be issued. Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant to be issued, REMAND to Commissioner. Court ordered cash bail forfeited.

Defendant Terry Miller Jr in court.  Attorney Sarah Zwach in court as a friend of the court for Terry Miller Jr.  Attorney Dennis Murphy in court on behalf of Patrick J Anderson for State of Wisconsin. 
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Sarah Zwach to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $120.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $50.00 per month beginning on December 1, 2022 and then the 1st of each month there after.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept. Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed. Case is adjourned for a Preliminary Hearing ins Preliminary Hearing Court.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 26, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Terry Miller in court in person.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Defendant appears without counsel and is not SPD Eligible. Court orders the case adjourned for CAUSE for an Indigency Hearing.
  Indigency hearing scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Orlando AC; Juancarlos C-P and 2414 N. Oakland Ave.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 2 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.

Defendant Terry Miller in court with attorney Heather L. Johnson.  Defendant Terry Miller in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Terry Miller appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Swanson, Branch 11.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.   DEFENDANT IS NOT INDIGENT. Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).
